    ,
    
    "source" :
    
    
    "Incorrect handling of air conditioning servicing equipment."
    ,
    
    "consequences" : [
    
    
    
    "Unnecessary damage to the environment due to emerging refrigerant."
    
    ]
    ,
    
    "actions" : [
    
    
    
    "Before connecting the filling system to the air-conditioning system, make sure that the manual shut-off valves are closed."
    ,
    
    
    "Before disconnecting the filling system from the air-conditioning system, make sure that the process is complete so that no refrigerant can escape into the atmosphere."
    ,
    
    
    "After the purified refrigerant has been filled into an external compressed gas bottle from the filling system, the manual shut-off valves on the bottle and on the filling system should be closed."
    ,
    
    
    "Do not expose the filling system to moisture or use in a damp environment."
    ,
    
    
    " Shut off the power supply at the filling system before carrying out maintenance work."
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "                     An extension cable with cross-sectional area of at least 2.5 mm                     <sup>2</sup>                      should be used only when absolutely necessary.                 "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    
    "In the case of fire, the external bottle should be removed."
    ,
    
    
    "Fill the oil extracted from the air-conditioning system into a suitable closable container (the refrigerant oil contains small quantities of refrigerant)."
    ,
    
    
    "The filling system must be secured to prevent it from rolling away. "
    ,
    
    
    "Set down and use the air conditioning servicing equipment with refrigerant R1234yf only in cool, well-ventilated places."
    ,
    
    
    "Protect from heat and direct sunlight and do not set down and use in areas with temperatures above 50 °C."
    ,
    
    
    "Do not set down and use in or near cellars or other lower-lying areas."
    ,
    
    
    "Only set down and use in areas with adequate air flow (complete air exchange at least once per hour in the workshop area and 3 times per hour in lower-lying areas, e.g. in assembly groups)."
    
    ]
    
